 location I have seen a comment like report to server after 2 sec).<br /> 4. Scenarios<br /> a. Playing station 28 tid 11 offset 0 length 180 sec (suppose current time 10:10:00)<br /> Played for 30 sec.<br /> Offset stored in localstorage offset 30 sec <br /> Song expiration set in local storage current time + (length &ndash; offset) ie 10:10:40 +(180-30) = 10:13:10 <br /> b. Sent new station request<br /> c. Checked the offset if 0 start playing if not check expiration time if its more than current time start playing otherwise play ondeck song<br /> Playing station 38 tid 22 offset 0 length 120 sec ( current time 10:10:40)<br /> Played for 90 sec<br /> Offset stored in local storage : offset 90 sec<br /> Song expiration set in local storage current time + (length &ndash; offset) ie 10:12:10 +(120-90) = 10:12:40 <br /> d. Sent new station request<br /> e. Checked the offset if 0 start playing if not check expiration time if its more than current time start playing otherwise play ondeck song<br /> Playing station 38 tid 22 offset 0 length 120 sec ( current time 10:12:40)<br /> Played for 10 sec<br /> Offset stored in local storage : offset 10 sec<br /> Song expiration set in local storage current time + (length &ndash; offset) ie 10:12:50 +(120-10) = 10:14:30 <br /> f. Returning back to the station 28<br /> g. Checked the offset if 0 start playing if not check expiration time if its more than current time start playing otherwise play ondeck song<br /> in this case the offset is 30 sec and expiration time is 10:13:10 <br /> but current time is 10:12:50 so it is less than the expiration time srat playing tack from offset.<br /> This is assumed flow can be implemented on webplayer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl66" style="text-align: center;" height="60">2</td>\r\n<td class="xl76" style="text-align: center;" width="81">PAR-250</td>\r\n<td class="xl75" style="text-align: center;"><a title="Plumbing " href="http://jira.mspot.com/browse/PAR/component/11906">Plumbin